comments: McDaniels (MIN) establishes himself in Bullock's (DAL) path and does not deliver contact.
Doncic (DAL) is moving alongside Edwards's (MIN) path as he hedges the pick and marginal body contact occurs during Edwards's (MIN) drive.
Wood (DAL) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Wood (DAL) makes contact with the ball during McDaniels' (MIN) shooting motion and dislodges the ball before incidental arm contact occurs.
Edwards (MIN) places his forearm on Hardaway jr.'s (DAL) side and marginal body contact occurs during his drive to the basket.
Edwards (MIN) moves alongside Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path with a collapsed forearm and marginal body contact occurs as he contests the driving shot attempt.

Hardaway Jr. (DAL) brushes Edwards' (MIN) chin during his normal upward shooting motion toward the basket, causing incidental contact to occur.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed incidental when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
McDaniels (MIN) is moving alongside Doncic's (DAL) path and marginal body contact occurs during Doncic's (DAL) drive.
Doncic (DAL) releases his pass attempt prior to stepping into the backcourt.
Bullock (DAL) establishes himself in McDaniels' (MIN) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
McDaniels (MIN) is moving alongside Doncic's (DAL) path and marginal body contact occurs during Doncic's (DAL) drive.
McDaniels (MIN) places his hands against Doncic's (DAL) chest and marginal contact occurs during rebounding.
Edwards (MIN) dribbles the ball on the sideline. Possession should have been awarded to DAL.
Edwards (MIN) places a stayed hand to Dinwiddie's (DAL) side and marginal contact occurs as Edwards (MIN) releases away during the drive.
Wood (DAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) extends his arm and makes contact with McDaniels' (MIN) face as he is landing from his jump shot attempt.
Doncic (DAL) makes contact with Gobert's (MIN) arm and the contact affects his ability to gather the loose ball.
Gobert (MIN) engages with Powell (DAL) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Gobert (MIN) releases away to retrieve the entry pass.
Gobert (MIN) turns to roll and incidental foot to foot contact occurs with Powell (DAL) as Powell (DAL) goes to hedge the pick.
Bullock (DAL) legally contests Edwards's (MIN) jump shot attempt.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Edwards (MIN) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Rivers (MIN) and Dinwiddie (DAL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Russell (MIN) moves in a direct path up the court and absorbs the contact initiated by Hardaway Jr. (DAL), who veers back into him in the frontcourt.
Gobert (MIN) establishes himself in Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path and does not deliver contact.
Powell (DAL) brings his arm toward Russell's (MIN) path and marginal contact occurs during Russell's (MIN) drive.
After the made shot attempt, Gobert (MIN) and Powell (DAL) come together in the lane and marginal contact occurs.
Russell (MIN) grazes Hardaway Jr. (DAL) before making clean contact with the ball. A jump ball is correctly assessed.
Russell (MIN) reaches around Doncic (DAL) and initiates contact that affects his SQBR during his drive.
Bullock (DAL) and Edwards (MIN) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Edwards (MIN) brings his off-arm toward Hardaway Jr. (DAL) and marginal contact occurs as Edwards (MIN) releases away without applying any force.
Doncic (DAL) moves underneath Gobert (MIN) as he is airborne and initiates contact that dislodges him from his rebounding position.
McDaniels (MIN) wraps two hands around Powell's (DAL) waist off-ball and the contact affects his FOM.
Russell (MIN) commits a take foul on Dinwiddie (DAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
